One person died instantly and four others were injured following an accident on Nairobi-Mombasa highway involving a truck and a pick up.   The accident occurred at Kiunduani after the pick up heading to Makindu collided with the truck which was headed to the opposite direction. The injured were rushed to Makindu sub-county hospital for treatment. A source at the facility said two were transferred to Kenyatta National Hospital in critical condition. Makueni county commissioner Maalim Mohammed has blamed truck drivers for causing most of the accidents along the highway. "We know they drive carelessly and that is why we are loosing lives every other time," he told the Star on phone. The body was taken to Makindu sub-county hospital mortuary. Read: Seven killed after lorry collides with hearse at Sultan Hamud Â  Click here for the latest political news